SIMPLE: grapple
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grapple
<hw>Grap"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Grappled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Grappling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>grappiller</ets>, OF. <ets>graypil</ets> the grapple of a ship, fr.
<ets>graper</ets> to pluck, prop., to seize, clutch; of German origin.
See <er>Grape</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To seize; to lay fast hold
of; to attack at close quarters: as, to grapple an antagonist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To fasten, as with a grapple; to fix; to join
indissolubly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The gallies were <qex>grappled</qex> to the Centurion.</q>
<rj><qau>Hakluyt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Grapple</qex> them to thy soul with hoops of steel.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grapple</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Grapple
<hw>Grap"ple</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To use a grapple; to contend in
close fight; to attach one's self as if by a grapple, as in wrestling;
to close; to seize one another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To grapple with</b></col>, <cd>to enter into contest
with, resolutely and courageously.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And in my standard bear the arms of York,⟦br⟧
To <qex>grapple</qex> with the house of Lancaster.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grapple</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Grapple
<hw>Grap"ple</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See Grapple, <pos>v. t.</pos>,
and cf. Crapple.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A seizing or seizure; close hug
in contest; the wrestler's hold.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An instrument, usually with hinged
claws, for seizing and holding fast to an object; a grab.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A grappling iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The iron hooks and <qex>grapples</qex> keen.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Grapple plant</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a South
African herb (<spn>Herpagophytum leptocarpum</spn>) having the woody
fruits armed with long hooked or barbed thorns by which they adhere to
cattle, causing intense annoyance.</cd> -- <col><b>Grapple
shot</b></col> <fld>(Life-saving Service)</fld>, <cd>a projectile, to
which are attached hinged claws to catch in a ship's rigging or to hold
in the ground; -- called also <altname>anchor
shot</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grapplement</ent>⟦br⟧
